{
  "stem": "9.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was another typical thing when I was a child was a fish for Saturday.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We would buy a live fish and let it swim in the bathtub.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I had a ball with that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I observed the chicken-- chicken, excuse me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Fish.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And on Friday, the fish was killed, had to be scaled, cleaned, and cooked.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And sometimes we just cooked steaks and sometimes we made what we call gefilte fish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Gefilte fish means filled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That's all it means.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We would cut out the pieces of meat from the steak of the fish, grind it like for a meatloaf, put some onions and bread crumbs and eggs into it, and fill the steaks back again, and poach it.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was an awful lot of work, a lot of bones to cope with while eating.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But that was a quite a typical dish, because the fish that we used was very cheap and was caught in the local rivers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was carp, K-- C-A-R-P.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Today when we make gefilte fish, it's never from carp alone, because carp is very fat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "What we do, we use a little carp for the taste and add on white fish to it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we do make twice a year gefilte fish, but they're balls, not steaks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We make them for holidays.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the whole family here that's available now, whatever is left-- we call everybody a family that we know almost-- and they enjoy it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All I remember from holidays, that my parents went to services.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to have a seat on the eastern wall was the most important thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only the rich people could afford it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The women were sitting upstairs and the men downstairs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Women had very little-- they weren't recognized at all.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
